com.assylias.jbloomberg

Interface ResultParser<T extends RequestResult>


  • public interface ResultParser<T extends RequestResult>
    A ResultParser parses the responses received from the Bloomberg Session after having sent a request. Once the final response has been received, the noMoreMessage method must be called to allow the parser to start its parsing job.

    This interface has been made public for convenience but users should not need to implement it.

    All implementations are thread safe.

      • getResult

        T getResult()
                                  throws InterruptedException
        Returns:
        the result of the parsing of all the received messages. This method blocks until a result is available
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the noMoreMessages has not been called yet
        InterruptedException - if the thread is interrupted before the result has been received and parsed
        com.bloomberglp.blpapi.InvalidRequestException - if the response returned by Bloomberg reports an error - this can typically happen if the request was malformed (which should not happen if this API is used properly) or the service is down.

      • getResult

        T getResult(long timeout,
          TimeUnit unit)
                                  throws InterruptedException,
                                         TimeoutException
        Parameters:
        timeout - the maximum time to wait
        unit - the time unit of the timeout argument
        Returns:
        the result of the parsing of all the received messages. This method blocks until a result is available or the specified waiting time elapses.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the noMoreMessages has not been called yet
        InterruptedException - if the thread is interrupted before the result has been received and parsed
        com.bloomberglp.blpapi.InvalidRequestException - if the response returned by Bloomberg reports an error - this can typically happen if the request was malformed (which should not happen if this API is used properly) or the service is down.
        TimeoutException - if the specified waiting time elapses before the result could be computed
